---
title: Pork and Veggie Bibimbap with Zucchini, Carrots & Jasmine Rice
description: This dish takes its name from the Korean word for mixing rice. Which is exactly what you’re meant to do after serving it: put your rice in a bowl, add the toppings, and mix it all together so that those flavors and textures combine in a glorious mishmash. There are plenty of flavors and textures going on here, too, like sweet carrot, mighty mushrooms, and pork tossed with garlic, ginger, and soy sauce.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pork-and-veggie-bibimbap-a29a40a2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pork-and-veggie-bibimbap-5e67d7511082fd2292725cfc-b71b9a88.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-and-veggie-bibimbap-5e67d7511082fd2292725cfc
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 78 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1190 mg
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @Carrots{6%oz}. Using a #peeler{},
shave carrots lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go. Trim and halve
@Zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Peel and
mince @Ginger{1%thumb}. Mince @Garlic{2%cloves}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%tsp},
and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally, until
ready to serve. In a separate small bowl, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tbsp}, half
the @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1%tbsp}, and up to half the @Sriracha{2%tsp}
to taste. Stir until sugar has dissolved.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tbsp} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots; season with @salt{} and
@Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove
from pan and set aside. Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add zucchini;
season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side. Remove from pan and set aside with carrots.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@Ground Pork{10%oz}, ginger, and garlic. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add remaining soy
sauce and cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper; divide between
bowls. Arrange pork and veggies on top. Top with pickled scallion whites
(and pickling liquid). Drizzle with sauce and remaining sriracha to taste.
Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.